### Queries vs Mutations

Queries are used to fetch data without side effects, while mutations modify data on the server. Use queries for read operations and mutations for create, update, or delete operations.

```typescript
// Query - read only
query GetUser {
  user(id: "123") {
    id
    name
  }
}

// Mutation - modifies data
mutation CreateUser {
  createUser(name: "John") {
    id
    name
  }
}
```

**Common interview trap:** Confusing mutations with queries when handling state changes.

